00:01:57.000 --> 00:02:00.000
Now what, you will ask, has Beethoven got 

00:02:00.000 --> 00:02:02.000
to do with our anniversary? A lot; and I'll 

00:02:02.000 --> 00:02:05.000
tell you why. I have been looking at the 

00:02:05.000 --> 00:02:07.000
opening programs played by both 

00:02:07.000 --> 00:02:11.000
orchestras back there in 1842, and I 

00:02:11.000 --> 00:02:13.000
found one striking similarity between 

00:02:13.000 --> 00:02:17.000
them: the name of Beethoven is 

00:02:17.000 --> 00:02:20.000
all over the place. 

00:02:24.000 --> 00:02:27.000
He had the market cornered, 

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:29.000
